                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/><persName><name type="cognomen" key="Chio">Chio</name></persName>
                    </ab>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="face" n="b">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>onum</ex></expan>
                    </ab>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="face" n="c">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>edit</ex></expan>.
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>Chio gave this as a gift.</p></div>

            <div type="commentary">
            <p>One of eight Carrara marble vessels dedicated by Chio at the Sanctuary of Diana
                    Nemorensis. The vessel is solid and so could not have been used as a container.
                    As for the inscription, the precise meaning of 'Chio' is unclear: Guldager Bilde
                    argues that the name Chio is a Latinized form of Χίων, 'from Chios', and
                    therefore he must have been a wealthy freedman. Guldager Bilde also suggests
                    that the vessel was used in a hero-cult context in honor of Hippolytos.</p></div>
            

